{
  "stem": "25598.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Bessarabia and Bukovina, all of them were-- most of them were in the field, other than those who managed to escape with the Russians eastwards, when the Russians withdrew from the Germans or men in arm.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Which, by the way, my Aunt [INAUDIBLE], her husband and her baby did.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They managed to escape with the Russians deeper into the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Unfortunately, in one of the train stations where they went down for water, she was getting very tired.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She had a one-year-old son.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was getting tired holding the baby, and she gave the baby to her husband to hold the baby.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was a, a bombing of the train, and her husband and the baby were killed in front of her eyes.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the rest of the people who remained alive were shoved into the train.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the train took off back to the end of Russia, where she spent, with her mother-in-law, four years all by herself.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, she and her mother-in-law, working hard in the-- but at least there was no danger from the Nazis there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we crossed the Dniester on a barge into a territory which was called by the Germans, at that time, Transnistria, meaning on the other side of the river Dniester.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This name did not exist on a map.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Germans and the Romanians made it up, and it only existed for four years.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When-- when the territory was reconquered by the Russians in 1944, the name of this large territory disappeared.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's a territory as big as Nova Scotia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's 16,000 square miles, with hundreds of villages and towns, all of which became camps.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And all of which were, by the way, inhabited by many local Ukrainian Jews.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
